                     DarkWind Profession Workers

    Workers allow players to concentrate on their adventures while still
bringing in materials to work on later. In the profession building, 4e, n
from Center of Town, you can '|GKBhire|000' or '|GKBfire|000' workers, as well as
type '|GKBworkers|000' for a list of your workers.

    Syntax:
      hire <profession> <target> <amount> <repeat?>
      fire <profession> <#>
      workers

    Worker professions:
      herbalism - hires a worker for herb terrain
      mining    - hires a worker for ore terrain
      skinning  - hires a worker for hides by creature race
      fishing   - hires a worker for fish-part reagents by fishing terrain
      reagent   - hires a scavenger for saved reagents by creature race

    The workers cost between 1000 and 5000 coins. The more you pay, the
more materials they're likely to bring back. It's no guarantee however,
and there's always the chance they'll pocket some and just claim that's
all there was to be found. If you hire them to repeat the job, they'll
go back out over and over as long as you have the funds to pay them,
unless it's close to reboot time, then they'll take a break. They will
repeat every 15 minutes. They will take funds directly from your bank
account, so you will have to make sure you can fund them as long as you
want them to go out.

    If you want them to stop working for you, you can fire them. You can
type '|GKBworkers|000' to get a list of your workers, then fire the # of worker
|000you wish to fire. The # of the worker will increment over the course of
|000the boot, and is not an indication of your personal worker count.

    Currently, every player can get 1 worker for each profession. At HERO
you can hire another worker, then another at LEGEND, and finally one more
at the maximum level (250). You also get 1 worker when you reach 500 in
the profession, then 1 more when you reach 1000. That is a max of 6
workers per profession.
Reagent scavengers use your level-based worker count because they are not
tied to a single profession skill. You can't double up the same worker
target for the same profession. If you're a ghost, linkdead, or relogged
while your worker was out, you will not receive any materials.
